    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-09T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="952"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d952">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/16670: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-09T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 9, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>318. Chungking’s 224, June 6, noon. The Department assumes that you will
                    supplement your recent representations (your 771, June 5, 9 p.m.<note n="35"
                        xml:id="d952fn1">Not printed, but see Ambassador Grew’s despatch No. 5645,
                        June 10, together with enclosures, <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_713">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, pp. 713</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_715">715</ref>.</note>) with a further
                    emphatic protest against this endangering of personnel and premises of the
                    American Embassy. You may wish to point out that any further recurrence will not
                    comport with the assurances of the War Minister<note n="36" xml:id="d952fn2"
                        >Gen. Hideki Tojo.</note> mentioned by Mr. Matsuoka in your 781, June 6, 8
                        p.m.<note n="37" xml:id="d952fn3">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Tokyo via Shanghai. Repeated to Chungking, Peiping, Hankow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
